{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-27","name":"Erik Nielsen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm","nameForms":[{"lang":"da","fullText":"Erik Nielsen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Erik"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Nielsen"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Suffix","value":"Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Erik Nielsen Gyldenstierne","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1310–1378","fullLifespan":"about 1310–about 1378","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/tijdm/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7758-130078-5529-94/dist.png?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/186438577","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7758-130078-5529-94/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7758-130078-5529-94/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1310","birthPlace":{"address":"Denmark","geo":{"latitude":56.0,"longitude":10.0,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1378","deathPlace":{"address":"Denmark","geo":{"latitude":56.0,"longitude":10.0,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"burialPlace":{"address":"Denmark","geo":{"latitude":56.0,"longitude":10.0,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"in 1328, with his brother Jep Nielsen af ​​Eskjær, seals the land deed issued by Eskild Jensen (Udsøn) to Mr. Niels Brok at Viborg County Council, and then both sealed it with the arms of the Gyldenstierners; this Erik Nielsen must not be confused with Erik Nielsen Markalk, who in 1340 owned property in Horns herred (Høgholt and Bjørnholt) and was a Banner, who is stated to have fallen in 1345; appears, on the other hand, in 1345 in King Valdemar's obligation of 6 Jan. and 16-17. Jan. in fact, together with his father-in-law Peder Vendelbo, in 1345 he was a co-lawyer for King Valdemar in the deed of cession issued by him in Skåne, Halland and Blekinge, as well as in 1344 a co-lawyer for the settlement between the king and Counts Henrik and Claus; probably replaced Erik Nielsen Banner as marshal and is described as such in 1347 at the division of the inheritance after the elder Peder Vendelbo, again in 1349 as a matter of fact and again in 1353 at the settlement between King Valdemar and Counts Henrik and Claus at Vinninge Å, but is described in 1355 as former marshal, and knight (here for the first time), when he testifies to having the deed to King Valdemar for his farm in Ø. Velling; He then held Næsbofjerding as a fief of the king, acquired a large amount of property with the intention of placing it under his farm Aagaard, sealed the recess in Kalundborg in 1360, is mentioned again in 1378 as knight Erik Nielsen to wit with Otte Snafs.\n1347-53 March. Inherited 25 March 1347 Peder Vendelbo's estate in Grensten S. [ 5 ]","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1310","date":"about 1310","place":"Denmark"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1330","date":"1330","place":"Denmark","age":"20","id":"KLXQ-FZQ"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1339","date":"about 1339","place":"Denmark","type":"Spousal","age":"29","id":"GZGX-7C7"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1340","date":"about 1340","place":"Denmark","age":"30","id":"LHGH-MK2"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1359","date":"about 1359","place":"Denmark","age":"49","id":"GZGX-7C7"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1378","date":"about 1378","place":"Denmark","age":"68"},{"name":"Burial","sources":"0","place":"Denmark"}],"parent":[{"name":"Sir Niels Erikssen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1255–1330","birthDate":"A+125