cilia Pedersdatter Vendelbo在丹麥結婚。他們至少是1個兒子和1個女兒的父母。他去世於大約1378年在他的家鄉享年70歲，埋葬在丹麥。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1310–about 1378":"大约1310年–大约1378年","1270–Female":"1270年–殁","1300–1341":"1300年–1341年","1305–1355":"1305年–1355年","1310–1378":"1310年–1378年","1310–Female":"1310年–殁","1319–1359":"1319年–1359年","1340–1388":"1340年–1388年","–Female":"殁","1255–1330":"1255年–1330年","1275–Female":"1275年–殁","1330":"1330年","1275":"1275年","1341":"1341年","1340":"1340年","1350":"1350年","1270":"1270年","1305":"1305年","1359":"1359年","1378":"1378年","about 1339":"大约1339年","1388":"1388年","1355":"1355年","1300":"1300年","1255":"1255年","1310":"1310年","about 1359":"大约1359年","about 1378":"大约1378年","about 1310":"大约1310年","1319":"1319年","about 1340":"大约1340年","Denmark":"丹麦","lifeSummary":"当Erik Nielsen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm于大约1310年出生在丹麦时，他的父亲Sir Niels Erikssen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm57岁，母亲Edel Pedersdatter Saltensee11308岁。他于大约1339年与Cecilia Pedersdatter Vendelbo在丹麦结婚。他们至少是1个儿子和1个女儿的父母。他去世于大约1378年在他的家乡享年70岁，埋葬在丹麦。"},"hr":{"about 1310–about 1378":"oko 1310.–oko 1378.","1270–Female":"1270–preminula","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"1310–1378","1310–Female":"1310–preminula","1319–1359":"1319–1359","1340–1388":"1340–1388","–Female":"preminula","1255–1330":"1255–1330.","1275–Female":"1275–preminula","1330":"1330.","1275":"1275","1341":"1341","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","about 1339":"oko 1339.","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","about 1359":"oko 1359.","about 1378":"oko 1378.","about 1310":"oko 1310.","1319":"1319","about 1340":"oko 1340.","Denmark":"Danska"},"cs":{"about 1310–about 1378":"okolo 1310–okolo 1378","1270–Female":"1270–Zesnulá","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"1310–1378","1310–Female":"1310–Zesnulá","1319–1359":"1319–1359","1340–1388":"1340–1388","–Female":"Zesnulá","1255–1330":"1255–1330","1275–Female":"1275–Zesnulá","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1341":"1341","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","about 1339":"okolo 1339","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","about 1359":"okolo 1359","about 1378":"okolo 1378","about 1310":"okolo 1310","1319":"1319","about 1340":"okolo 1340","Denmark":"Dánsko"},"da":{"about 1310–about 1378":"omkring 1310–omkring 1378","1270–Female":"1270–Afdød","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"1310–1378","1310–Female":"1310–Afdød","1319–1359":"1319–1359","1340–1388":"1340–1388","–Female":"Afdød","1255–1330":"1255–1330","1275–Female":"1275–Afdød","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1341":"1341","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","about 1339":"omkring 1339","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","about 1359":"omkring 1359","about 1378":"omkring 1378","about 1310":"omkring 1310","1319":"1319","about 1340":"omkring 1340","Denmark":"Danmark"},"nl":{"about 1310–about 1378":"circa 1310–circa 1378","1270–Female":"1270–Overleden","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"1310–1378","1310–Female":"1310–Overleden","1319–1359":"1319–1359","1340–1388":"1340–1388","–Female":"Overleden","1255–1330":"1255–1330","1275–Female":"1275–Overleden","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1341":"1341","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","about 1339":"circa 1339","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","about 1359":"circa 1359","about 1378":"circa 1378","about 1310":"circa 1310","1319":"1319","about 1340":"circa 1340","Denmark":"Denemarken"},"en":{"about 1310–about 1378":"about 1310–about 1378","1270–Female":"1270–Deceased","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"1310–1378","1310–Female":"1310–Deceased","1319–1359":"1319–1359","1340–1388":"1340–1388","–Female":"Deceased","1255–1330":"1255–1330","1275–Female":"1275–Deceased","1330":"1330","1275":"1275","1341":"1341","1340":"1340","1350":"1350","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","about 1339":"about 1339","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","1255":"1255","1310":"1310","about 1359":"about 1359","about 1378":"about 1378","about 1310":"about 1310","1319":"1319","about 1340":"about 1340","Denmark":"Denmark","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nielsen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Niels, Jorgen, Knud, Lars, Nels, Bent, Borge, Holger, Ove, Einer, Oluf.","Danish, Norwegian, and North German: patronymic from the personal name <i>Niels</i>, a shortened form of <i>Nikolaus</i> (see   Nicholas  ). Compare   Nielson  ,   Neilsen  ,   Nelsen  ,   Nilsen  , and   Nilson  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Nicholas","meanings":["English (southwestern England and south Wales) and Dutch: from the personal name <i>Nicholas</i> (from Latin <i>Nicolaus</i>, from Greek <i>Nikolaos</i>, from <i>nikān</i> ‘to conquer’ + <i>laos</i> ‘people’). Forms with <i>-ch-</i> are due to hypercorrection (compare   Anthony  ). The name in various vernacular forms was popular among Christians throughout Europe in the Middle Ages, largely as a result of the fame of a 4th-century Lycian bishop, about whom a large number of legends grew up, and who was venerated in the Orthodox Church as well as the Catholic. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Croatian and Serbian <b>Nikolić</b> (see   Nikolic  ), Greek <b>Papanikolaou</b> ‘(son of) Nicholas the priest’ and   Nikolopoulos  . Compare   Nickolas  .","History: The colonial official and revolutionary patriot Robert Carter Nicholas was from a prominent VA family on both sides. His father was a British navy surgeon who emigrated <i>c.</i> 1700 from Lancashire, England, to Williamsburg, VA."]},{"name":"Neilsen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik, Ejnar, Gurli, Jorgen, Nels, Niels.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Nielsen  . Compare   Neilson   3.","Scottish (Midlothian): variant of   Neilson   1."]},{"name":"Nelsen","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Nels, Erik, Einer, Berger, Folmer, Holger, Iver, Juel, Morten, Thor, Uffe.","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Nielsen   or   Nilsen  . Compare   Nelson  .","Flemish and German: patronymic from   Nelis  ."]}]},{"name":"Erik","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Later variant of   Eirik  , now in frequent use, especially in Sweden."],"variants":[{"name":"Eric","meanings":["Of Old Norse origin, from <i>ei</i> ‘ever, always’ (or <i>einn</i> ‘one, alone’) + <i>ríkr</i> ‘ruler’ (  see  Eirik   ). It was introduced into Britain by Scandinavian settlers before the Norman Conquest. As a modern given name, it was revived in the mid 19th century and has remained in use since."]},{"name":"Eirik","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Eirikr</i>, a compound of <i>ei</i> ‘ever, always’ (or <i>einn</i> ‘one, alone’) + <i>ríkr</i> ‘ruler’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1353273,"age":40,"year":"1350","julianDay":2214138,"description":"Plague ravishes Denmark and Sweden.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Erik Nielsen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm was born about 1310, in Denmark, his father, Sir Niels Erikssen Gyllenstierna af Svaneholm, was 57 and his mother, Edel Pedersdatter Saltensee, was 11308. He married Cecilia Pedersdatter Vendelbo about 1339, in Denmark. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died about 1378, in his hometown, at the age of 70, and was buried in Denmark."},"et":{"about 1310–about 1378":"umbes 1310–umbes 1378","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1305–1355":"1305–1355","1310–1378":"131